HEADWORD: Midwifery
<hw>Mid"wife`ry</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The art or practice of assisting women in childbirth;
obstetrics.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Assistance at childbirth; help or cooperation in
production.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

